# MD Documentation Sync

When making frontend or backend changes, **update the relevant MD files** in the repo root and ecom-back:

## Files to Update

| When | Files |
|------|-------|
| **Service/feature changes** | `SERVICE_STATUS.md`, `SERVICE_DETAILED_PROGRESS.md` |
| **Overall progress** | `PROJECT_PROGRESS_SUMMARY.md`, `PHASE_COMPLETION_CHECKLIST.md` |
| **Release/launch** | `LAUNCH_PLAN.md`, `RELEASE_ASAP_CHECKLIST.md` |
| **Scope changes** | `V1_SCOPE.md` |
| **Service API changes** | `ecom-back/<service>/API_DOCS.md` |

## Conventions

- Update `Last updated:` date (format `YYYY-MM-DD`) at top of each modified file.
- Add dated entries to `SERVICE_DETAILED_PROGRESS.md` Change Log for notable changes.
- Update % complete in `SERVICE_STATUS.md` when service/frontend progress changes.
- Mark completed checklist items with `[x]` in `PHASE_COMPLETION_CHECKLIST.md`.
- Keep `ecom-storefront` as primary frontend; `ecom-frontend` (Vite) is deprecated.
